  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by reason of scale, siting, design, bulk, mass and appearance would be an undesirable addition,&amp;nbsp;representing an overly dominant and excessive addition to the dwelling. The side extension would be significantly visible from public vantage points and would be visually intrusive, represent poor design and would be out of character in the context of the area.&amp;nbsp; The excessive depth of the rear extension combined with the addition of the side extension will result in overdevelopment of the site.&amp;nbsp; As such, the proposal would cause undue harm to the character and appearance of the host dwelling and surrounding area, including to the historic distinctiveness of the Becontree Estate. The proposal is therefore contrary to the following policies which seek to ensure that development recognises local character and promotes good design whilst protecting and enhancing historic environments:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: &quot; pt=&quot;&quot; sans&quot;,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;-\r\nNational Planning Policy Framework &lt;/span&gt;National Planning Policy Framework\r\n(NPPF) (&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt&quot;&gt;MHCLG&lt;/span&gt;, 2024)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot; pt=&quot;&quot; sans&quot;,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;- Policy D4 of the\r\nLondon Plan (March 2021)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: &quot; pt=&quot;&quot; sans&quot;,=&quot;&quot; sans-serif;&quot;=&quot;&quot;&gt;- The Residential\r\nExtensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (February 2012)&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&l